# Bulk Oxygen and Carbon Dioxide Supply Solicitation

## Synopsis

Public Service and Procurement Canada (PSPC) is inviting offers for the supply, installation, and removal of oxygen and carbon dioxide storage tanks, as well as the supply of oxygen and carbon dioxide for Natural Resources Canada (NRCan). This solicitation cancels and replaces previous solicitation WS4324136155-AM, dated February 28, 2024.

## Call to Action

Offerors are required to submit their bids electronically, and all supporting documentation must be received by PSPC by June 19, 2024, at 14:00 EDT (Eastern Daylight Time). Late bids will not be considered responsive.

## Procurement Details

*   **Procurement Category**: Goods and Services
*   **Notice Type**: Request for Proposal (RFP)
*   **Procurement Method**: Competitive - Open Bidding
*   **Selection Criteria**: Lowest Price
*   **Trade Agreements**: Canadian Free Trade Agreement (CFTA)
*   **Regions of Delivery**: National Capital Region (NCR)
*   **Contracting Entity**: Department of Public Works and Government Services (PSPC)
*   **End User Entity**: Department of Natural Resources (NRCan)

## Contact Information

Offerors may contact PSPC's project lead, Richard Tea, at <richard.tea@tpsgc-pwgsc.gc.ca> for any questions or concerns related to this solicitation.

## Additional Resources

The solicitation document, including all attachments and amendments, is available on the Ariba Discovery platform under reference WS4324136155-GD.

## Key Dates

*   **Publication Date**: May 21, 2024
*   **Tender Closing Date**: June 19, 2024 (14:00 EDT)
*   **Expected Contract Start Date**: March 31, 2024
*   **Expected Contract End Date**: March 31, 2027
